                    "created": "2010-01-19T01:37:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-19T01:37:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38686",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tech13",
                        "name": "tech13",
                        "displayName": "Michael Rehbein",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "As per: http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.log.filters.html\r\n{quote}\r\nWhen you add one or more Filters to the Log object, the message must pass through all of the Filters before any Writers receives it. \r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nTherefore, when you filter the way you did, the error must both be Zend_Log::EMERG and Zend_Log::INFO at the same time.\r\n\r\nCurrently, Zend_Log_Filter doesn't support an \"Or\" filter.\r\n\r\nAnother way to handle it is to filter for all the priorities you do not want.\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tech13",
                        "name": "tech13",
                        "displayName": "Michael Rehbein",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-23T10:54:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-23T10:54:45.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
